    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-08-06T15:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-08-06T15:45:00-05:00" n="419"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/3126: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-08-06T15:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 6, 1924—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>157. My 150, July 30, 11 a.m.<note n="8" xml:id="d419fn8">Not printed.</note> I
                    have just received from the Minister for Foreign Affairs a note of some length
                    in which it is stated that the Government of Nicaragua declines to accept the
                    suggestion made by the Government of the United States that Dr. Dodds and
                    certain assistants be requested to come to Nicaragua to assist in the
                    elections.</p>
                <p>A translation of the pertinent part of the note will be cabled as quickly as
                    possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
